==Abstract==

This IIP introduces the "sendheaders" message which requests that a peer announce new blocks via headers messages rather than inv messages. It is adapted from BIP 130 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Headers-first synchronization is more efficient:
* Headers contain proof-of-work, allowing validation before downloading blocks
* Reduces round-trips for block announcements
* Enables parallel block downloads

==Specification==

===sendheaders Message===

<pre>
sendheaders message: (empty)
</pre>

After receiving sendheaders, a node SHOULD announce new blocks with "headers" messages instead of "inv" messages.

===Behavior===

Before sendheaders:
<pre>
Node A: discovers block
Node A -> B: inv(block_hash)
Node B -> A: getheaders(locator)
Node A -> B: headers(block_header)
</pre>

After sendheaders:
<pre>
Node A: discovers block
Node A -> B: headers(block_header)
</pre>

===Headers Message Limit===

A headers message may contain up to 2000 headers.

